Sorry for the delay- here is our next ENROLLMENT CONTEST! This one is a little different in that it will run for the next 4 weeks with similar prizes for winning. Each contest will end every Monday like usual.
Enrollment Contest #9! Now through Monday, August 3rd.
Anyone who turns in a completed enrollment application OR refers a student that completes an enrollment application will be entered into a drawing to win one chair, one small prize, and one bag of candy from the pictures shown. Each week the winner drawn can choose one of each!
Bonus entry for turning in all paperwork with application (current proof of residence and birth certificate). You'll get one entry for every new student you refer!

As you can see from our posts, Stark students SOAR all the way to the finish line- graduation is possible no matter what has happened along the way ğŸ“ğŸ’›ğŸ’™

shared_text:
Stark Cchs Canton
June 11 at 9:29 AM Â·

Some things about Stark High School that make us GREAT:

*We provide a clean, safe learning environment with smaller classroom settings.
*We focus on the WHOLE student and provide support based programs, weekly mentoring, counseling, case management opportunities, and much more!
*Flexible schedules for our adult students. We know there is a reason you have gotten behind and we want to do everything we can to support you to reach your graduation goal!
*Online curriculum and distance learning plans. In addition to our amazing teaching staff, we have multiple options for students to learn and complete their credits.
*Opportunities to give back to the community. Students can participate inâ€¦ More

I can only speak for myself, and Iâ€™ll admit Iâ€™ve been rattled during this time. My anxiety has risen, my motivation to complete daily tasks has plummeted and my moods have varied as significantly as Ohio weather on a spring day.

And thatâ€™s someone thatâ€™s still able to go to work and maintain a somewhat-regular routine. I think about how others must be feeling as their entire life has become turned upside down. Research has shown a substantial correlation to unemployment and negative mental health effects along with rising use of opioids,â€¦

Canton City School District
April 17 at 7:48 AM Â·

PSA for our families (not a school district service): Winter crisis assistance with utility bills that are in disconnect (excluding water) has been extended to 5/1/2020 because of COVID-19. You may qualify if you meet income guidelines. All appointments are conducted over the phone there are various was to submit your needed documents.
PIPP is a monthly payment plan based upon household gross income.
HEAP is a one time payment plan toward your heating source.
To make appointments:
https://capappointments.com/CapAppointments.aspx
Or call 330-617-1055

shared_text:
Parma Campus-CASTLE High School
April 7 at 5:05 PM Â·

Students always say they hate math, they canâ€™t do math and that they always make mistakes in math causing them to shut down and give up. What they do not understand or realize is:

They are not the only ones who make mistakes in math
There is a lot that can be learned from our own mistakes as well as the mistakes of others
Precise thinking and problem-solving skills are necessary to be successful which grow over time and with continual practice and support
Math is all around us and is seen everywhere

Look through the images below that have been found throughout the years in various advertisements, websites, stores/restaurants and additional real-world instances.

What do you notice? What do you wonder? Can you find the errors in each image?

(If you find, take a picture of and share an example of a math error in the real world, you will earn 10 class dojo points)
